  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2012-01-25",
    "date": "2012-02-06T22:02:32Z",
    "text": "Airline First Responder Workplace Fairness Act - Directs the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to establish an Aviation Rulemaking Committee to develop recommendations for the Administrator to include in a final rule to minimize flight attendant fatigue.\n\nRequires the Committee to comprise aviation safety experts, labor representatives, and industry stakeholders.\n\nDirects the Administrator to issue regulations to minimize flight attendant fatigue."
  },
